# Fan Club Z Development Guidebook

## 1. Architecture & Technology

- **Frontend**: React + TypeScript (web/mobile), Zustand for state, TanStack Query for data fetching.
- **Mobile**: Expo/React Native, mobile-first, Apple-style UI, SafeAreaProvider.
- **Backend**: Node.js microservices, RESTful APIs, OpenAPI 3.0.3, API Gateway routing.
- **Database**: Supabase (PostgreSQL), Redis for caching, S3 for file storage.
- **Blockchain**: Smart contracts (Solidity/Rust), escrow, on-chain settlement.
- **CI/CD**: GitHub Actions, automated versioning, Snyk/code scanning.

## 2. Code Style & Structure

- Use TypeScript everywhere; prefer interfaces over types.
- Functional, declarative programming; avoid classes.
- Modularize code, avoid duplication.
- Use RORO (Receive an Object, Return an Object) pattern.
- Place static content and types at file end.
- Use Prettier for formatting.

## 3. UI/UX Standards

- **Mobile-first**: All screens and components must be optimized for mobile.
- **Apple-style**: Use Apple-inspired, medium-size UI elements, consistent button styling.
- **Safe Areas**: Use SafeAreaProvider and SafeAreaView for all layouts.
- **Accessibility**: ARIA roles, native accessibility props, text scaling.
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS (web), styled-components or Tailwind for React Native, Shadcn UI, Radix UI.
- **Component Patterns**: Use declarative JSX, functional components, minimal useEffect/useState.

## 4. API & Data

- **API**: Only use endpoints defined in OpenAPI spec. Validate all responses.
- **Data Validation**: Use Zod for runtime validation.
- **Error Handling**: Early returns for errors, log with Sentry/expo-error-reporter.
- **Security**: JWT auth, RBAC, rate limiting, input validation, secret management.

## 5. Testing & QA

- **Unit Tests**: 80%+ coverage, Jest/React Native Testing Library.
- **Integration Tests**: All API endpoints, run in CI.
- **E2E Tests**: Critical user journeys (login, bet creation, wallet), run after every change.
- **Test Data**: No demo users; use production-like data only.
- **Test Execution**: Run one test suite at a time; ensure all services (Supabase, Redis) are operational on default ports before tests.
- **QA**: Smoke, regression, and stress testing required for every feature/bugfix.

## 6. Security & Compliance

- Follow OWASP Top 10, regular penetration and smart contract audits.
- Use secure storage for secrets and user data.
- Enforce HTTPS, proper session and access control.
- Regularly review and update security checklist (see ADR Appendix D).

## 7. Git & Versioning

- Use automated scripts for branch, commit, push, merge, and release (see git_versioning_automation.md).
- Feature branches from develop; PRs required for main.
- Use semantic versioning; update changelog on every release.

## 8. Deployment

- Use CI/CD for build, test, security scan, and deploy.
- Run `npm run db:migrate` and `npm run db:seed` before starting dev server.
- Start frontend with `cd client && npm run dev`.

## 9. Documentation

- Document all code, APIs, and architecture.
- Maintain up-to-date README and ADRs.
- Follow Expo/Next.js documentation best practices.

## 10. Key Conventions

- Never invent endpoints or use demo users.
- Always validate environment variables.
- Prioritize security, performance, and user experience.
- Default to recommended options and best practices.
- All main pages/components must use mobile-optimized, Apple-style classes.

